case_circumstances:
An employee of the West Side Market found the decedent in the washroom of the West Side Market.  Cleveland Police and Fire Depts. were notified and the man was conveyed to Lutheran Medical Center where he was pronounced dead at 12:12 p.m. on 12-27-1974.
The man had an additional condition:  Probable diabetes mellitus with clycosuria and ketonuria.
case_clothing_on_body: Blue denim jacket with red trim and white sleeves; gray short-sleeved pullover sweater, white T-shirt, olive green pants, black leather belt
case_footwear: Black leather shoes with blk/white laces, royal blue and white socks.
case_other_items_with_body: 1 key, $1.16 in cash, piece of candy cane, piece of sausage found in coat pocket.
dental: Dental information / charting is currently not available
documents: There are currently no documents available for this case.
